rComments: I had to meet this lab coordinator, because I needed to change my lab schedule. She was extremely rude and vile. I have never met such a horrible person at UofT before!! The best word that describes her is 'witch'.

Did not have her as a direct lecturer, only a lab coordinator, but felt the need to review her here anyway.  She has a horrible attitude for an educator - extremely condescending, treats you like a child, and a stupid child at that.  She is in the wrong line of work, dealing with students, and should be doing administrative or research work only.
Very unhelpful. Very poor communication skills.

Horrible. Today was my first time seeing her in person, and hopefully the last. She is very condescending and it seems as though she's out to get students, not help them. She ridicules you for not knowing the answer - um, that's why I'm there! She makes you so frustrated/mad at her you feel like crying or hitting something. She's just terrible.
seem like a nice lady in the labs ....
One of the worst teachers ever. Horrible attitude, no smiles, nothing. Her questions to me made me feel like an idiot. Dear Prof., if we could answer every question you ask, we would be teaching too.
One word to describe her rhymes with hitch....
she will make you cry if you ask her a question.
OK, when she talks, it feels like she hates everybody. But she should really know that we ALL hate her too. How old is she - I thought she was old enuff to be polite!
shes mean :(

After twice of deliberately waiting an hour before her office opens, just to ask her some questions, I realized that she was not paid to smile at students. However, it's all good. She would develop fewer wrinkles talking with an expressionless face.
VERY VERY MEAN. First year students, you better not bump into this lady. If you have small problem with her, your whole semester of CHM138 will be MISERABLE. Just stay away from her.

Very mean! She clearly needs to respect students a lot more. I had to ask her for help several times during the course, and every time she made me feel very miserable. I will now think ten times before seeing her in person again.
She's mean.
Insistent on inconvenient office hours. However, helpful when you haver a problem.

A feared lab coordinator.  You never want to ask questions cos you are scared of getting yelled at.  I feel that she has a hidden disdain for coordinating for the 100 level CHM course - but was unable to find a better job

i hope she gets fired.  she makes chem miserable.  this lady does not understand that some ppl have labs/class/tests during her office hours... apparently it's our fault if we don't SKIP class to see her... learn to make alternate arrangements!
She makes the labs scary.... but at least she keeps the lab in good order...
unhelpful and totally unapproachable..
